title: For Sale/Trade:  AK47 Egyptian Maadi RPM ACC/Intrac import
postcontent:
1 of only 2000 ever imported into the USA.
The RPM is an Egyptian rifle made with Egyptian parts, and is the closest we will probably get to the Russian AK47.
 Made at the Factory 54 which is stamped on the bottom.
This one is dated 1994  ACC/Intrac import Maadi RPM. This variant was brought in only from 1994-1995 and has a 20 inch chrome lined,threaded barrel . All small parts are numbered and matching.

One of the only semi-automatic Kalashnikovs imported into the United States, in almost every regard, an exact duplicate of the Russian AKM. During the 1950’s the Soviet Union, as part of its military aid program, established the production of Soviet-pattern small arms in the Arab Republic of Egypt.

More info here: http://www.ar15.com/forums/t_4_81/143966_Egyptian_Maadi_Ak47_Guide.html

Comes with ATI Fiberforce black Synthetic buttstock, I.O. black clubfoot style stock set, plus 2 original and hard to find Egyptian Maadi 30 round steel mags, 2 Tapco 30 round mags.

No shipping any where.
FTF transfer with bill of sale to MISSOURI residents.

title: For Sale:  LIKE NEW Remington 700 chambered in 300 BLK w/scope
postcontent:
I have a basically brand new Remington 700 in 300 blackout with a Nikon P-series 300BLK scope.
I bought this gun new at the beginning of summer and had the scope professionally mounted and bore-sighted by a gunsmith.  It has a threaded barrel (in case you ever want to throw on a suppressor) and a Hogue overmolded stock.  I bought it to take into less than ideal treestands while deer hunting so I did't scratch the expensive walnut stock on my primary rifle.  
I took it to the range and shot ONE box of ammo out of it.  Its a blast to shoot.  Low recoil and almost no muzzle blast.  Its the perfect short treestand gun because of the Hogue stock.  It doesn't get scratched and is grippy, so even with gloves its easy to carry up and down ladders.  

THE ONLY REASON I'M SELLING IS I NEED MONEY FOR SCHOOL. 
THIS GUN IS PERFECT AND LOOKS LIKE IT JUST CAME OUT OF THE BOX.  
I want to keep it but I decided to go back for another degree so a few toys have to go.

I have about 80 rounds of 125gr custom loaded softpoints for hunting that I will sell for $50 extra.  I paid $1 per round for them from a custom shop.

From their website:
Product Description
remington Chambered for the incredibly popular 300 AAC Blackout, this rifle features the time-proven Model 700 action and is designed to impress from the bench or in the field at a very affordable price. At the core of the Model 700 SPS Tactical 300 Blackout is the machined solid-steel, cylindrical Model 700 receiver design, ensuring uniformity, strength, and solid bedding area. Unique to this precision rifle is the 16.5" inch, heavy-contour clean barrel threaded to accept AAC and all 5/8 x 24 threaded flash hiders, muzzle brakes, and suppressors. The tactical-style carbon steel, hammer-forged barrel is the perfect balance between handling in tight spots and delivering pinpoint accuracy. With a twist rate of one in seven inches, this rifle is optimized for accuracy. These specialty, bolt-action rifles are shipped with a thread protector installed. The rock-solid barreled action is bedded in a Hogue OverMolded, Ghillie Green, pillar-bedded, synthetic stock with a semi-beavertail fore-end for added stability. The soft-touch, sure-grip stock is extremely comfortable for extended, long range shooting and assures a positive grip in both stressful situations and inclement weather. The dual point pillar-bedding guarantees a solid interface between the action and stock to help insure cold bore accuracy and prevent point-of-impact shifts. Add Remington's X-Mark Pro externally-adjustable trigger, designed to break-like-glass and set at 3.5 pounds from the factory, and this rifle delivers surgical accuracy.
